title: Two arrested after woman raped on central London street
text:
Two men have been arrested after a semi-conscious woman was found just moments after she had been raped in central London.

The woman was found by officers Sicilian Avenue, Holborn at 3.40am today.

The crime scene has been preserved and forensic officers have been searching for evidence.

A woman was raped at 3.40am today on Sicilian Avenue in Holborn, central London. Officers found the 'semi-conscious' victim. Police later arrested two men who are currently in custody

According to Scotland Yard: 'On Saturday, October 19 at around 3.40am police on patrol in Sicilian Avenue came across a semi-conscious female.

'The woman they believe had been raped.

'Two men [no further details] were arrested at the scene and are currently in custody at Central London police stations.

'Enquiries are ongoing.'
